nie ||  || \n|-valign=\"top\"\n| Film || align=\"center\" |2014 || Ron and Laura Take Back America || Bob Zackie ||  ||\n|-valign=\"top\"\n| TV series || align=\"center\" |2015 || ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]'' || Cert ||Loser Like Me || 1 episode \n|-valign=\"top\"\n| TV series || align=\"center\" |2015 || Good Job, Thanks! || John McWayne || Hacked! || 1 episode \n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|id=0120160}}\n* {{tcmdb name|id=24981|name=Jim J. Bullock}}\n* {{IBDB name}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20121004234145/http://www.lortel.org/LLA_archive/index.cfm?search_by=people&first=Jim&last=Bullock&middle=J. Jim J. Bullock] at [[Internet Off-Broadway Database]]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bullock, Jim J.}}\n[[Category:1955 births]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Wyoming]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Texas]]\n[[Category:American male comedians]]\n[[Category:21st-century American comedians]]\n[[Category:American male film actors]]\n[[Category:American male stage actors]]\n[[Category:American male television actors]]\n[[Category:American television talk show hosts]]\n[[Category:American male voice actors]]\n[[Category:Gay actors]]\n[[Category:LGBT entertainers from the United States]]\n[[Category:LGBT Baptists]]\n[[Category:LGBT comedians]]\n[[Category:LGBT people from Texas]]\n[[Category:LGBT people from Wyoming]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Lee Strasberg Theatre and Film Institute alumni]]\n[[Category:Oklahoma Baptist University alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Casper, Wyoming]]\n[[Category:People from Odessa, Texas]]\n[[Category:People with HIV/AIDS]]\n[[Category:Southern Baptists]]\n[[Category:Permian High School alumni]]\n", "name_user": "Moe1810", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eFilmography", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jim_J._Bullock"}
{"title_page": "Dogan K\u0131m\u0131ll\u0131", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{more footnotes|date=September 2015|blp=yes}}\n{{Orphan|date=September 2015}}\n}}\n\n'''Dogan K\u0131m\u0131ll\u0131''' is an architect and former Mayor of [[Isparta]] (Birth 19 June 1939 Isparta), [[Turkey]].\n\n== Early life ==\n\nHe attended primary and middle school in Isparta and completed high school in [[Kayseri]], Turkey.  He later earned a Bachelor of Science degree in Architecture from the department of Macka Faculty of Architecture at [[Istanbul Technical University]] in 1961. \nUpon completion of his degree, he performed his military service where he was a reserve officer.  He received architectural training at the Kagithane School of Military Engineers and at [[Tekirdag]] 571st Civil Engineering Unit from 1962\u20131964.\n\n== Architecture ==\n\nIn 1966 he began his professional career by starting Kimilli Insaat Taahhut as an independent architect. His company sought contracting work in construction and provided architectural drawings.\n\nAs a founding member of the Aksu Energy and Trading Corporation, his company produced electrical energy that supplied government enterprises.\n\n== Politics ==\n\nThroughout his life, he remained devoted to public service.  In 1977, he was elected Mayor of Isparta from the [[Justice Party (Turkey)|Justice Party (AP)]].\n\nHe was supported by 70.01% of the voters and served from 1977 to 1980. From 1996\u20131999, he served as City President of the Isparta [[True Path Party (Turkey)|True Paty Party (DYP)]].\n\n== Personal life ==\n\nDogan currently resides with his wife, Yuksel, in Isparta, Turkey.  He has 3 sons and 8 grandchildren.\nHe continues to work in the fields of energy, wood products, construction and contracting.\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.yerelnet.org.tr/belediyeler/belediye_secimsonuclari.php?yil=1977&belediyeid=128480|title= ISPARTA BELED\u0130YES\u0130 - BELED\u0130YE BA\u015eKANLI\u011eI SE\u00c7\u0130M SONU\u00c7LARI|work=www.yerelnet.org.tr}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.yerelnet.org.tr/belediyeler/belediye_baskanlar.php?belediyeid=128480|title= ISPARTA BELED\u0130YES\u0130 - \u00d6NCEK\u0130 BA\u015eKANLAR|work=www.yerelnet.org.tr}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kimilli, Dogan}}\n[[Category:Justice Party (Turkey) politicians]]\n[[Category:20th-century Turkish politicians]]\n[[Category:Democrat Party (Turkey, current) politicians]]\n[[Category:Turkish architects]]\n[[Category:Istanbul Technical University alumni]]\n\n\n{{Turkey-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{more footnotes|date=September 2015|blp=yes}}\n{{Orphan|date=September 2015}}\n}}\n\n'''Dogan K\u0131m\u0131ll\u0131''' is an architect and former Mayor of [[Isparta]] (Birth 19 June 1939 Isparta), [[Turkey]].\n\n== Early life ==\n\nHe attended primary and middle school in Isparta and completed high school in [[Kayseri]], Turkey.  He later earned a Bachelor of Science degree in Architecture from the department of Macka Faculty of Architecture at [[Istanbul Technical University]] in 1961. \nUpon completion of his degree, he performed his military service where he was a reserve officer.  He received architectural training at the Kagithane School of Military Engineers and at [[Tekirdag]] 571st Civil Engineering Unit from 1962-1964.\n\n== Architecture ==\n\nIn 1966 he began his professional career by starting Kimilli Insaat Taahhut as an independent architect. His company sought contracting work in construction and provided architectural drawings.\n\nAs a founding member of the Aksu Energy and Trading Corporation, his company produced electrical energy that supplied government enterprises.\n\n== Politics ==\n\nThroughout his life, he remained devoted to public service.  In 1977, he was elected Mayor of Isparta from the [[Justice Party (Turkey)|Justice Party (AP)]].\n\nHe was supported by 70.01% of the voters and served from 1977 to 1980. From 1996-1999, he served as City President of the Isparta [[True Path Party (Turkey)|True Paty Party (DYP)]].\n\n== Personal life ==\n\nDogan currently resides with his wife, Yuksel, in Isparta, Turkey.  He has 3 sons and 8 grandchildren.\nHe continues to work in the fields of energy, wood products, construction and contracting.\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.yerelnet.org.tr/belediyeler/belediye_secimsonuclari.php?yil=1977&belediyeid=128480|title= ISPARTA BELED\u0130YES\u0130 - BELED\u0130YE BA\u015eKANLI\u011eI SE\u00c7\u0130M SONU\u00c7LARI|work=www.yerelnet.org.tr}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.yerelnet.org.tr/belediyeler/belediye_baskanlar.php?belediyeid=128480|title= ISPARTA BELED\u0130YES\u0130 - \u00d6NCEK\u0130 BA\u015eKANLAR|work=www.yerelnet.org.tr}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kimilli, Dogan}}\n[[Category:Justice Party (Turkey) politicians]]\n[[Category:20th-century Turkish politicians]]\n[[Category:Democrat Party (Turkey, current) politicians]]\n[[Category:Turkish architects]]\n[[Category:Istanbul Technical University alumni]]\n\n\n{{Turkey-politician-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: 1962-1964 \u2192 1962\u20131964 (2)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dogan_K%C4%B1m%C4%B1ll%C4%B1"}
